<SLUG> BC-HKN-COYOTES-NOTEBOOK-AZR </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
TOCCHET THINKING EXTENSION 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by N.Y. Times News Service clients)  
 By BOB MCMANAMAN  
 c.1998 The Arizona Republic  
<TEXT>
<P>
   EDMONTON, Alberta _ Jumping out to one of the best starts in his
career and staying healthy again has got veteran forward  &UR; Rick
Tocchet thinking about staying in the NHL possibly until he turns
40.
</P>
<P>
   His two-year contract, which pays him $2.15 million this season,
expires in July. He has an option to return for a third year, which
he almost certainly will do _ if he isn't given an extension before
then.
</P>
<P>
   ``What I'm proud of is I've worked very hard to get back where I
am,'' said Tocchet, who with eight goals and 19 assists entering
Wednesday's game against the Oilers was on pace for his best season
since 1992-93, when he scored 109 points for Pittsburgh.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's taken me a lot of summers to get where I can compete,
where I can be a good player again,'' he said.
</P>
<P>
   The 34-year-old Tocchet, who had a history of back problems
before joining the Coyotes last season, told the ``Edmonton
Journal'' that his improved health and the quality, young players
on the Coyotes makes him want to play for a long time.
</P>
<P>
   ``If there's something to be said, then I'll say it. The kids
here, they want to improve, so they listen,'' Tocchet said. ``That
makes my job easier, actually.'' &QL; 
Roster moves &QL; 
As expected, defenseman  &UR; Jason Doig has been activated from the
injured list and has been cleared to play by the Coyotes' medical
staff after missing all of training camp and the first two months
of the regular season because of a torn pectoral muscle.
</P>
<P>
   The 6-foot-3, 220-pound Doig was assigned to Springfield of the
AHL for a two-week conditioning stint. After that, the Coyotes must
either recall him to Phoenix or risk losing him on waivers if they
decide to keep him in the minors.
</P>
<P>
   In another move, the Coyotes announced that left wing  &UR; Louie
DeBrusk has been reassigned from Las Vegas of the IHL to
Springfield. DeBrusk, obtained during the summer from Tampa Bay in
the  &UR; Craig Janney trade, had two goals, eight points and 134
penalty minutes in 17 games with the Thunder. &QL; 
Slap shots &QL; 
The Coyotes' defensive trio of  &UR; Teppo Numminen, Keith Carney and
 &UR; Jyrki Lumme rank in the top five in the NHL in takeaways. Numminen
entered Wednesday's game third overall with 37. Carney and Lumme
each had 36, tying them for fourth.
</P>
<P>
   For the eighth consecutive game, Coyotes enforcer/right wing
 &UR; Jim Cummins was a healthy scratch. Defenseman  &UR; Gerald Diduck was
back in the lineup after missing two games with a bruised
shoulder. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
