<P>
   HEALTH-FEET _ For more than seven years, Rick Waits, 47, watched
his world shrink. Struggling with a painful foot condition, he
could no longer play golf or even take weekend strolls with his
wife. And although he didn't complain, the couple realized his
problem was getting worse over time, limiting their activities and
creating a chronic, sedentary lifestyle. But after having an
experimental treatment that uses shock waves to mend minor bone and
tendon problems, he is walking again; able to play golf and, most
importantly, take weekend strolls with his wife. (Lore, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH PHOTO. MOVED
