<HEADLINE>
A FELINE FANTASY UNDER THE TREE 

</HEADLINE>
  
 (For use by New York Times News Service clients)  By JEANNIE KEVER 
c.1998 Houston Chronicle 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   You've browsed the gift catalogs for the super-rich, scanned
Martha Stewart's seasonal entertainment guides, sneered at the
neighbor's go-for-broke decorating scheme.
</P>
<P>
   You think you've seen it all.
</P>
<P>
   You're wrong.
</P>
<P>
   The holiday money-making machine has churned out another idea,
this one aimed at that favorite feline on your list. Turns out when
it comes to cats, it's not the gift that counts, it's the gift
wrap.
</P>
<P>
   The Michigan-based Kong Company has introduced catnip-scented
wrapping paper, saturated in fresh catnip nectar and sealed to
preserve the scent.
</P>
<P>
   The stuff is alleged to be so powerful that it comes with a
warning: Don't put a gift wrapped in the paper under the tree until
you're ready for the cat to rip into it.
</P>
<P>
   It's pricey _ $3.49 for a 9-inch by 12.5-inch sheet. But if
you're game, call the company at 303-216-2626 for more
information. &QL; 
 &QL; 
 &QL; 
XXXXEND OF STORY &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-12-03-98 1347EST &QL; 
</TRAILER>
