<P>
   GA-MEDICAID _ATLANTA _Georgia's Medicaid program has expanded
its rules on payment for physician assistants, paving the way for
more medical services in rural areas. The DMA now will reimburse
care delivered by PAs in what are designated ''remote sites'' in
medically underserved areas. DMA officials cited a clinic in South
Georgia whose closing was the subject of a J-C article in August.
In closing the Willacoochee clinic, its operators blamed the
Medicaid policy that would not reimburse PAs at a private clinic
that was not designated a hospital outpatient center or a ''rural
health center.'' (Miller, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
