<P>
   FBC-SEC-CHAMPIONSHIP _ ATLANTA _ The SEC championship game has
served as a springboard to the national championship in the past,
and it appears to be the same this year. Tennessee is unbeaten and
ranked No. 1 in the nation and will secure a spot in the national
title game with a victory over Mississippi State. In the first SEC
title game in 1992, Alabama used the SEC title as a springboard to
its last national championship. Florida advanced to the national
title game after winning the SEC title, losing to Nebraska in '95
and defeating Florida State in '96. Tennessee had its shot at a
national championship after winning the SEC last year, but lost to
Nebraska in the Orange Bowl. A look at the SEC title game and its
relation to the national title. (Barnhart, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution)
</P>
