<P>
   RUDOLPH _ANDREWS, N.C. _ FBI task force press briefing on the
search for Eric Rudolph. (Harmon, Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
</P>
<P>
   DDN-COX-SKOOLCHAPS _ DAYTON, Ohio _ Washington-based group
Americans United for Separation of Church and State has written
Brookville schools superintendent expressing opposition to ``public
school chaplaincy'' proposal school officials have been cautiously
exploring. The group says the concept is unconstitutional and they
promise a legal challenge if the school system decides to proceed.
School officials say no decision has been made, and they're still
gathering information on the pros and cons. If Brookville goes
forward, it may become the only school in the area to have a
chaplain. The idea pushes the envelope about religion in the
schools. (Kepple, Dayton Daily News)
</P>
<P>
   AUS-TEXAS-CONSTITUTION _ AUSTIN, Texas _A proposed new Texas
Constitution to be unveiled Friday by top lawmakers includes a
provision lengthening terms of office for legislators. The framers
want four-year terms for House members and six years for senators.
All lawmakers, however, would face term limits. (Herman, Austin
American-Statesman)
