publisher by market capitalization, said full-year profit will be 6
percent lower than a year ago, worse than expected, as sales in
some markets slow and costs rise. The Anglo-Dutch owner of the
Lexis-Nexis information service and Cahners Business Information
said pretax profit, excluding one-time items, will be 770 million
pounds (US$1.29 billion). Developing. (Roughton, Cox News Service).
