<P>
   FBN-PATRIOTS-STADIUM (Hartford, Conn.) _ As new questions arise
every day about the expense and feasibility of a stadium deal that
economists say will be the biggest giveaway in the history of
professional sports, Democratic lawmakers are growing increasingly
wary. But the governor and legislative leaders continue to push the
plan, even though they don't know for certain where the stadium
will be built or what it will cost. By Mike Allen.
</P>
