<TEXT>
<P>
   Here are the business news stories the Los Angeles Daily News
plans to move for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs
of Friday, Dec. 4 and thereafter. The stories will carry the ``f''
financial news category code unless otherwise noted. For questions
about stories, contact James Laurin at the Daily News, (818)
713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   PARAMOUNT-BILLION (Los Angeles) _ Paramount has broken through
the $1 billion mark in domestic box office for 1998 thanks to
``Titanic,'' ``Deep Impact,'' ``The Truman Show'' and ``Rugrats,''
joining Disney and Sony as the only studios to achieve the
milestone in a year. By Dave McNary.
</P>
<P>
   DOCTOR-GRADING (Los Angeles) _ Health Net releases its second
annual report card of physician groups. By Ben Sullivan.
</P>
<P>
   BAJA-FRESH (Los Angeles) _ The founder of Baja Fresh has sold
most of his restaurant chain to an investment group that plans to
aggressively accelerate its expansion plans. Baja Fresh is a
popular fast-food Mexican restaurant chain in Southern California
that eschews can openers, preservatives and processed food. By
Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
<P>
   MEGABUCK-HOMES (Los Angeles) _ More homes sold for a million
dollars or more during the third quarter of 1998 than any previous
three-month period in state history, a real estate information
company reported. By Gregory J. Wilcox.
</P>
