<P>
   SLAIN-COP-SON (Los Angeles) _ Only 7 years old, Dylon Brown was
the one who insisted he speak at the news conference, to stand tall
before the TV cameras and declare to the world how much he loved
his father, an LAPD officer shot over the weekend by a gang member.
By Peter Hartlaub. (Will move in the ``a'' national and ``n''
California news files.)
</P>
<P>
   DEMOCRAT-CONVENTION (Los Angeles) _ The committee that will
decide whether Los Angeles, Denver or Boston gets the Democratic
National Convention in 2000 will be in town for a final, three-day
visit to the city. By Rick Orlov. (Will move in the ``a'' national
and ``n'' California news files.)
