<HEADER>
A2082 &Cx1f; tth-z
u v &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI &LR;      12-03 0204
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BUDGET-SPOT-SPI </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Seattle Post-Intelligencer plans to move the following
stories for clients of the NYTimes News Service for editions of
Friday, Dec. 4, and thereafter. If you have any questions, please
call Bob Schenet at 206-448-8037.
</P>
<P>
   GATES-BABY (Seattle) _ Melinda Gates, wife of the world's
richest man, Microsoft chief Bill Gates, is pregnant.
</P>
<P>
   By Warren Wilson. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   BOEING-JOBS (Seattle) _ Who likely to be facing the ax _ and
when _ in the cutbacks announced by Boeing.
</P>
<P>
   By Bruce Ramsey. (Story will move in the ``f'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   FBN-SEAHAWKS (Seattle) _ Shawn Springs is having a Pro Bowl
season, but he is worried he'll be hurt in next week's voting by
players and coaches because of his early success and subsequent
lack of chances due to opponents throwing away from him. The Jets
won't, and Springs' efforts against Keyshawn Johnson will be on the
more intriguing elements of Sunday's game.
</P>
<P>
   By Clare Farnsworth. (Story will move in the ``s'' category.)
