<HEADER>
A2092 &Cx1f; tad-z
u l &Cx13;  &Cx11;  BC-ICICLE-LIGHTS04-COX     12-03 0317
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-ICICLE-LIGHTS04-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Icicle lights melting away from store shelves
 &HT;    By Chris Reinolds
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _ One of this year's hottest Christmas decorating items
_ icicle lights _ are evaporating from store shelves and merchants
in Atlanta and across the country have been caught off guard by
their unexpected popularity.
</P>
<P>
   ``They completely blew out of here yesterday,'' said Lynn
Edmondson, seasonal manager of the Alpharetta, Ga., Lowe's Home
Improvement.
</P>
<P>
   The icicle lights manufactured by several firms have been on the
market for the last two holiday seasons, but are selling like
wildfire this year, retailers said. The outdoor lights are
comprised of a series of separate short strands of lights that hang
vertically.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's a different look, more of a vertical look,'' Edmondson
said. ``The cascading are nice too.''
</P>
<P>
   Jule Schreffler, a spokesman at Lowe's headquarters in North
Wilkesboro, N.C., said the lights are sold out nationwide.
</P>
<P>
   ``We ordered a lot more this year in anticipation of this, but
we're out now,'' Schreffler said. ``We can't get any more.''
</P>
<P>
   Michael's Arts and Crafts in Kennesaw, Ga., still had some
icicle lights Thursday afternoon but they are selling out fast,
said Andrea Jennings, a Michael's floral designer.
</P>
<P>
   At the Sandy Springs Kmart, which also still has some in stock,
the lights are priced from $4 for eight feet and $10 for 16 feet.
Lights that flash in different sequences cost more.
</P>
<P>
   ``People can afford to do different things out here to their
houses,'' said clerk Paula Dodd.
</P>
<P>
   At The Christmas Shoppe in Atlanta, which also has some icicle
lights, owner Edward Touwsma said from a distance the lights really
do look like icicles.
</P>
<P>
   ``We bought three times the amount we normally do,'' Touwsma
said.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
