<HEADLINE>
BILL AND MELINDA GATES EXPECTING SECOND CHILD 
</HEADLINE>
   (For use by New York Times News Service clients.)  
 By WARREN WILSON  
 c.1998 Seattle Post-Intelligencer  
<TEXT>
<P>
   SEATTLE _ Microsoft chairman Bill Gates and wife Melinda Gates
are expecting their second child next summer.
</P>
<P>
   Family spokeswoman Rose Berg confirmed Thursday that the baby is
due in mid to late June.
</P>
<P>
   Melinda and Bill are ``very excited'' about the prospect of a
sibling for Jennifer Katharine, now 2 1/2, but plan to say little
else, preferring to keep family matters private, Berg said. They
don't know the baby's sex and don't plan to find out before he or
she is born.
</P>
<P>
   Bill Gates holds about one-fifth of the shares of Microsoft,
which he co-founded in 1975. At Thursday's closing price, those
shares were worth just under $63 billion.
</P>
<P>
   Melinda Gates is closely involved in the family's philanthropic
efforts, Berg said. Washington Gov. Gary Locke recently named her
co-chair of a new state commission on early childhood learning,
along with his wife, Mona Lee Locke.
</P>
</TEXT>
