<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-MSTATE-SEASON04-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Mississippi State season in review
 &HT;    By Leo Willingham
 &HT;    c. 1998 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   ATLANTA _
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE 42, VANDERBILT 0
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 5 at Starkville, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   The Bulldogs held Vanderbilt to 37 rushing yards in recording
their biggest margin of victory against an SEC foe in 62 years.
James Johnson rushed for 111 yards and a touchdown and Anthony
Derricks returned an interception 20 yards for a score. Record:
1-0.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE 14, MEMPHIS 6
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 12 at Memphis
</P>
<P>
   Johnson surpassed 100 yards in rushing for the second game in a
row, gaining 192 yards and scoring a touchdown. The Bulldogs
defense withstood a late rally to improve to 2-0. They would earn
their first Top 25 ranking of the season one day later. Record:
2-0.
</P>
<P>
   OKLAHOMA STATE 42, MISSISSIPPI STATE 23
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 19 at Stillwater, Okla.
</P>
<P>
   The Bulldogs defense was pounded for 561 yards, and Johnson was
held to 38 rushing yards in the nonconference loss. Kevin Prentiss
had a career-high 106 receiving yards, all but 73 of the team's 179
passing yards, but the Bulldogs were held to only 88 rushing yards.
Record: 2-1.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE 38, SOUTH CAROLINA 0
</P>
<P>
   Sept. 26 at Columbia, S.C.
</P>
<P>
   Prentiss returned the opening kickoff for a touchdown as the
Bulldogs improved to 2-0 in the SEC for the first time since 1986.
Johnson rushed for 144 yards and two touchdowns, including a
67-yard TD run in the first quarter. Record: 3-1.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE 38, AUBURN 21
</P>
<P>
   Oct. 10 at Starkville, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   Lakeside High graduate Robert Bean returned a blocked punt for a
touchdown and added an interception as the Bulldogs outscored
Auburn 24-7 in the third quarter. Bean's interception set up a
field goal by Brian Hazelwood and the 23-yard return of a blocked
punt was his first career touchdown. Record: 4-1.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE 53, EAST TENNESSEE STATE 6
</P>
<P>
   Oct. 17 at Starkville, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   Redshirt freshman Wayne Madkin passed for three touchdowns and
Johnson surpassed 100 yards rushing for the fifth game. The
Bulldogs had 427 yards of total offense and held the Buccaneers to
142 yards. Defensive end Edward Smith had a career-high 13 tackles.
Record: 5-1.
</P>
<P>
   LSU 41, MISSISSIPPI STATE 6
</P>
<P>
   Oct. 24 at Baton Rouge, La.
</P>
<P>
   The Bulldogs were looking for their first 4-0 start in the SEC,
but were dominated by the preseason favorite in the Western
Division. Johnson was held to 76 rushing yards, the second time in
seven games that he was held to less than 100 yards. Record: 5-2.
</P>
<P>
   KENTUCKY 37, MISSISSIPPI STATE 35
</P>
<P>
   Nov. 7 at Lexington, Ky.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson rushed for 209 yards, the second-best single-game
performance in school history, and surpassed the 1,000-yard plateau
for the second year in a row, the only player in MSU history with
two 1,000-yard seasons. But the Bulldogs were victimized by
Kentucky and Tim Couch, who passed for 338 yards and two
touchdowns, and dropped two games behind first-place Arkansas in
the SEC West. Record: 5-3.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE 26, ALABAMA 14
</P>
<P>
   Nov. 14 at Starkville, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   The Bulldogs ended their two-game losing streak as Johnson
rushed for 237 yards and two touchdowns, becoming the school's
single-season rushing leader. The victory, coupled with Arkansas'
28-24 loss at Tennessee, pulled the Bulldogs within one game of the
SEC West lead. Record: 6-3.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE 22, ARKANSAS 21
</P>
<P>
   Nov. 21 at Starkville, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   Hazelwood kicked five field goals, including a 27-yarder with
seven seconds remaining, to move the Bulldogs into a first-place
tie with the Razorbacks atop the division. Smith had three sacks
for the second consecutive game, and Madkin passed for 224 yards
and the team's lone touchdown. Record: 7-3.
</P>
<P>
   MISSISSIPPI STATE 28, MISSISSIPPI 6
</P>
<P>
   Nov. 26 at Oxford, Miss.
</P>
<P>
   Johnson had two short touchdown runs and North Atlanta graduate
Tim Nelson returned an interception 30 yards for a touchdown as the
Bulldogs clinched their first division title. Johnson, who was
already hampered by a groin injury, injured a shoulder on his
second touchdown run. Record: 8-3.
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
