<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-FBC-TEXAS-A&AMP;M-INJURY-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
INJURED QB FORCES CHANGE FOR TEXAS A&AMP;M
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By JIMMY BURCH 
c.1998 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Texas A&AMP;M quarterback Randy McCown will miss tomorrow's Big 12
championship game because of a broken left collarbone, coach R.C.
Slocum said yesterday.
</P>
<P>
   McCown, who will be replaced in the lineup by Stephenville's
Branndon Stewart, was injured during a fourth-quarter touchdown run
in last week's 26-24 loss to Texas. Because the initial pain was
not severe, no X-rays were taken at the time, and McCown was
cleared to practice in preparation for tomorrow's meeting between
No. 10 A&AMP;M (10-2) and No. 2 Kansas State (11-0) at 3:30 p.m. in St.
Louis.
</P>
<P>
   McCown reported increased pain during Wednesday's workout,
prompting trainers to X-ray the shoulder yesterday. That is when
the break was discovered, A&AMP;M officials said.
</P>
<P>
   ``He aggravated the injury Wednesday while throwing the
football,'' Slocum said. ``We'll miss him, but we've won a lot of
games with Branndon, too.''
</P>
<P>
   Stewart, a fifth-year senior who became a backup to McCown on
Oct. 3, has a career mark of 19-10 as A&AMP;M's starting quarterback.
He is 4-1 as a starter this season, including a 234-yard passing
performance Nov. 7 in place of an injured McCown in a 29-0 victory
over Oklahoma.
</P>
<P>
   Although he lacks McCown's scrambling abilities, Stewart has a
higher completion percentage (54.6) and a higher passing efficiency
rating (111.3) this season. He has completed 53 of 97 passes for
668 yards and four touchdowns, with only one interception.
</P>
<P>
   ``Branndon is excited, and the team has a lot of confidence in
him,'' A&AMP;M offensive coordinator Steve Kragthorpe said. ``I've been
chastised for saying this, but I've always said we've got a
quarterback luxury. We've won with both guys.''
</P>
<P>
   McCown, 6-1 as A&AMP;M's starter, missed the Oklahoma game because
of a separated right shoulder. That injury was unrelated to the
collarbone injury he suffered against Texas. Kragthorpe said McCown
is expected to miss three weeks, which would make him questionable
for a bowl game.
</P>
<P>
   A&AMP;M coaches said they would make no changes to the game plan to
account for Stewart's presence. But they have elevated punter Shane
Lechler, a quarterback in high school, to the role of Stewart's
backup and had him take snaps in practice yesterday. Ry Marek, a
freshman walk-on, would be the third-teamer, Kragthorpe said.
</P>
</TEXT>
