Classmates Amanda Schreck, left, and Diana Hancock guide Collin
Cassinat across campus. Born with a genetic disorder called
xeroderma pigmentosum, in which the cells of the body lack the
ability to repair DNA damage from ultraviolet rays, Collin's best
chance for survival is to avoid all sunlight. When not in the
classroom, Collin covers himself with a heavy blanket shield him
from the sun. (Michael Chow/The Arizona Republic Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT9) GILBERT, Ariz. -- Dec. 3, 1998 -- COLLIN-1-AZR, 12-2 --
Tinted windows at his home allow Collin Cassinat, 9, to look out at
