stage platform as the playing area, and only essential costumes and
props. All of which makes the show's theatricality more astonishing
and magical. (Andrea Mohin/New York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT3) NEW YORK -- Dec. 3, 1998 -- ADV. FOR SUN., DEC. 6 --
CANBY-THEATER-1, 12-03 -- John Turturro, left, and Tony Shalhoub in
the Classic Stage Company's ``Waiting for Godot.'' Samuel Beckett
is probably the only modern playwright whose works do not need, or
