   (NYT29) NEW YORK -- Dec. 3, 1998 -- BKN-BAVETTA-PROFILE, 12-03
-- Dick Bavetta, one of the best-known referees in the NBA, can't
wait to get back to his job. ``My body is crying out to me,
'Bavetta, what are doing speaking at a grammar school?' `` he says.
`` 'You should be in the Meadowlands.' It's just because I love
this more than anything. We'll get back.'' (G. Paul Burnett/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT28) TSURIT ARMY POST, Lebanon -- Dec. 3, 1998 -- ISRAEL-2,
12-03 -- Israeli Pvt. Gil Shalom strums his guitar at the Tsurit
army post just north of the Israeli border in southern Lebanon. In
the last two weeks, seven Israeli soldiers were killed in the
region by the Iranian-backed Hezbollah guerrillas. The spate of
funerals sparked anew what has been a cyclical re-examination of
the 20-year-old Israeli occupation of the Israeli ``security
strip'' along the Israeli-Lebanese border. (Rina Castelnuovo/New
York Times Photo)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT27) CASERTA, Italy -- Dec. 3, 1998 -- ITALY-PALACE, 12-03 --
Italian Air Force cadets march from the royal palace of Caserta.
Only 44 of the palace's 1,200 rooms are open to the public. Some
800 others are under military occupation by the Italian Air Force's
training school for non-commissioned officers. The palace's museum
director, the Culture ministry and art lovers want the military
out. But the air force argues they have no other place to go.
(James Hill/New York Times Photo)
</P>
