prodigal son. He refuses to come home. But he does drop in
occasionally to create new work and restage old ones for major
American ballet companies. More rarely, he visits with his own
troupe, now officially billed as Ballett Frankfurt on its tours,
and shows off a more anarchic side of his highly organized
choreography. By Anna Kisselgoff.
